# Cursor Rules - CrewAnywhere

Source of truth: local Markdown files and docs/ folder.

Always check before working:
- PROJECT_CONTEXT.md
- CURRENT_STATE.md
- DECISIONS.md
- TASKS.md
- docs/database/architecture.md (for DB work)

Also read (implementation truth):
- docs/ai/00_AI_INDEX.md and the files it links (ARCHITECTURE.md indexes docs/architecture, docs/auth, docs/database, docs/payments; plus FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md, DECISIONS.md, TECHNICAL_DEBT.md, NEXT_STEPS.md)

Keep .cursor/rules/project.mdc and CLAUDE.md consistent — update both when the doc sources change.

## Code Rules
- Next.js App Router patterns only
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind for all styling
- All DB changes via Supabase migrations only
- Atomic transition engine required for all state changes

## Architecture Rules
- Each domain module is self-contained
- Shared primitives live in shared/ - do not duplicate
- business_users and crew_users always kept separate
- No cross-domain imports except through shared layer

## Change Rules
- Explain what files you changed and why
- Keep changes minimal and scoped
- Ask before touching shared primitives or auth layer
- Add migration files for any schema changes
- Update DECISIONS.md for architecture choices
